body:
Once [flutter run --machine](https://github.com/flutter/flutter/pull/6645) lands, we should
* [support launching bazel targets](https://github.com/flutter/flutter-intellij/issues/392)
* update other launch targets to use `flutter run --machine` rather than `flutter daemon`

comment_data.body:
When we do this should we bump the version of flutter tools and up our minimum requirement?  Or should we support the old and the new worlds?

@danrubel @devoncarew
I recommend bumping the flutter tools version and requiring that version in IJ.

Sounds good.  Can we bump it when you have the (unrelated) new events work landed?  Or should we do it sooner?

/cc @danrubel
I'll address https://github.com/flutter/flutter/issues/6665 first, determine if there is anything else we need for this, then bump the number.

title: Update IntelliJ to use flutter run rather than flutter daemon
